CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 6, 1941, pg. 2 reads: "Prattis Asks About The Navy Problem - P.L. Prattis, executive editor of The Courier (extreme right) and Mrs. Roosevelt, at the Flyers' Club, County Airport, Thursday. Mr. Prattis questioned the First Lady on the Negro and the Navy. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: P. L. Prattis talking to Eleanor Roosevelt, with group of men and women, including Sara Limbach in background, gathered in the Flyers' Club, Allegheny County Airport
